<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/Annual-carnival-in-the-Belgian-city-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&#038;ssl=1" alt="UNESCO pulls Belgian carnival from heritage list over anti-Semitism charges" align="left" style="margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1" /> UNESCO on Friday withdrew an annual carnival in the Belgian city of Aalst from its heritage list over persistent charges of anti-Semitism. In an unprecedented move, UNESCO’s Intergovernmental Committee for the Safeguarding of Intangible Cultural Heritage said it was withdrawing the carnival “over recurring repetition of racist and anti-Semitic representations” at the event. The carnival of Aalst, in the Belgian Dutch-speaking region of Flanders, was initially added to UNESCO’s list of the intangible cultural heritage of humanity in 2010. Continue reading UNESCO pulls Belgian carnival from heritage list over anti-Semitism charges at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard